{%- comment -%}
  text-color-class — maps a `text_role` enum value to the corresponding
  `text-<role>` utility class. Single source of truth for the mapping.

  Emits NOTHING when the role doesn't bind a class on this element:
    - `inherit` — let CSS color cascade from a colored ancestor.
    - `none` — legacy alias for `inherit` (still used by _tab-head's
      schema). Treated identically.
    - `custom` / `palette` / `gradient` — the caller paints via an
      inline `--text` override AND a separate `text-primary` class
      (which reads `var(--text)`); this snippet doesn't emit that
      class either, since the caller is responsible for both pieces.
    - blank — same as inherit.

  Callers should `{% capture %}` the output and fall back to
  `text-primary` themselves when they need the inline-override route,
  so the `inherit` case (no class at all) stays distinct from the
  override case.

  Args:
    color_role — text_role enum value
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- if color_role != blank
  and color_role != 'inherit'
  and color_role != 'none'
  and color_role != 'custom'
  and color_role != 'palette'
  and color_role != 'gradient'
-%}
  text-{{ color_role }}
{%- endif -%}
